    "Unlike classical blockchains, that only allow blocks to specify a single parent block, determining the canonical chain exactly, a DAG allows blocks to reference multiple parents, but the order in which they are referenced can determine the canonical chain (e.g., by preferring the block referenced first).We consider three tie-breaking rule, which were analyzed before in the context of NC [23,46]."
  ]
